SIMPLE: expectorate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expectorate
<hw>Ex*pec"to*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Expectorated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Expectorating</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>expecrorare</ets> to drive from
the breast; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>pectus</ets>, <ets>pectiris</ets>,
breast. See <er>Pectoral</er>.]</ety> <def>To eject from the trachea or
lungs; to discharge, as phlegm or other matter, by coughing, hawking,
and spitting; to spit forth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expectorate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Expectorate
<hw>Ex*pec"to*rate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To discharge matter from
the lungs or throat by hawking and spitting; to spit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expectoration</ent>⟦br⟧
